    Frequent questions and answers

    Fully automated, fully supported

    Self-serve or work with a representative, we're here to help with the capital journey that works for you.

    • Signing up for mobile banking is easy! Simply download our app from the App Store or Google Play, and follow the registration process. You'll be able to create an account and access your finances right from your mobile device.
    • Yes, we prioritize the security of your transactions. We implement industry-leading encryption protocols to protect your sensitive data and ensure secure transactions. Our robust security measures and fraud detection systems provide an added layer of protection for your peace of mind.
    • Absolutely! Our platform allows you to make payments to accounts in other banks through convenient and secure transfer options. You can easily initiate transfers to recipients within the same country or even internationally, depending on the available services.
    • If you lose your mobile device, it's important to take immediate action. Contact our customer support team to report the loss and have your account temporarily disabled for security reasons. We can assist you in disabling access to your account from the lost device and help you regain access on a new device.
    • Setting up alerts and notifications is simple. Once you have logged into your account, navigate to the settings or preferences section. From there, you can customize the types of notifications you want to receive, such as balance updates, transaction alerts, and payment reminders. You can choose to receive notifications via email, SMS, or through our mobile app.
    • Yes, you can access your account from multiple devices. Our platform offers seamless multi-device synchronization, allowing you to log in and manage your finances from your smartphone, tablet, or computer. Your account information and transaction history will be up-to-date across all devices.
    • Yes, you can conveniently deposit checks using our mobile banking app. Simply access the app, select the "Deposit" option, and follow the step-by-step instructions to capture images of the front and back of the check. Once submitted, your check will be securely processed, saving you time and effort by avoiding the need to visit a physical branch.
